content.problem:
From a point 120 feet from the base of a tree, the angle of elevation 
to the top is $28°$. How tall is the tree?

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]
 % Ground
 (-1,0) – (13,0);

 % Tree
 (0,0) – (0,6);
 (-0.5,6) to[out=80,in=180] (0,7) to[out=0,in=100] (0.5,6);

 % Observer
 ll[AtlasTeal] (12,0) circle (4pt);

 % Line of sight
 (12,0) – (0,6.5);

 % Labels
 at (6,0) {120 ft};
 at (0,3.25) {$h$};

 % Angle
 (10,0) arc (180:153:2);
 at (9.3,0.8) {$28°$};
tikzpicture
center

From the top of a 150-foot lighthouse, the angle of depression to a 
boat is $12°$. How far is the boat from the base of the lighthouse?

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.35]
 % Water
 ll[blue!15] (-2,-1) rectangle (15,0);

 % Lighthouse
 ll[gray!30] (-0.5,0) rectangle (0.5,8);
 (-0.5,0) – (-0.5,8) – (0.5,8) – (0.5,0);

 % Lamp
 ll[yellow!70] (0,8.5) circle (0.3);

 % Boat
 (12,-0.3) to[out=0,in=180] (13,0) to[out=0,in=180] (14,-0.3);
 (13,0) – (13,1);

 % Horizontal line from top
 (0.5,8) – (8,8);

 % Line of sight
 (0.5,8) – (13,0);

 % Labels
 at (-0.5,4) {150 ft};
 at (6.5,-0.3) {$d$};

 % Angle of depression
 (2.5,8) arc (0:-12:2);
 at (3.2,7.3) {$12°$};
tikzpicture
center

A surveyor measures the angle of elevation to the top of a mountain 
as $35°$. She then moves 500 meters closer (along a straight line 
toward the mountain) and measures the angle of elevation as $42°$. 
How tall is the mountain?

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]
 % Ground
 (-1,0) – (14,0);

 % Mountain
 ll[gray!30] (0,0) – (0,8) – (1,8) – (3,0) – cycle;
 (0,0) – (0,8) – (3,0);

 % Positions
 ll[AtlasTeal] (12,0) circle (4pt);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (7,0) circle (4pt);

 % Lines of sight
 (12,0) – (0,8);
 (7,0) – (0,8);

 % Labels
 at (9.5,0) {500 m};
 at (3.5,0) {$x$};
 at (0,4) {$h$};

 % Angles
 (10.5,0) arc (180:146:1.5);
 at (9.8,0.6) {$35°$};
 (5.8,0) arc (180:138:1.2);
 at (5,0.7) {$42°$};
tikzpicture
center

From the top of a 200-foot building, the angle of depression to the 
bottom of a nearby flagpole is $50°$ and the angle of elevation to 
the top of the flagpole is $20°$. How tall is the flagpole?

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.35]
 % Ground
 (-1,0) – (13,0);

 % Building
 ll[gray!20] (0,0) rectangle (1.5,10);
 (0,0) – (0,10) – (1.5,10) – (1.5,0);

 % Flagpole
 (10,0) – (10,6);
 (10,6) – (10.5,6) – (10.5,5.5);

 % Horizontal from building top
 (1.5,10) – (11,10);

 % Lines of sight
 (1.5,10) – (10,0);
 (1.5,10) – (10,6);

 % Labels
 at (0,5) {200 ft};
 at (10,3) {$h$};
 at (5.5,0) {$d$};

 % Angles
 (3.5,10) arc (0:-50:2);
 at (3.8,8.5) {$50°$};
 (4,10) arc (0:20:2.5);
 at (5.5,10.8) {$20°$};
tikzpicture
center
